note: Dimensions of original manuscript: 155 x 95 (100 x 50) mm bound to 160 x 100 mm.
Laid, non-European paper; no visible chain lines

msIdentifier.repository: Kislak Center for Special Collections, Rare Books and Manuscripts

msContents.summary: Illustrated story of Yūsuf va Zulaykhā.

supportDesc.foliation: Modern pagination added in pencil, upper outer corners; catchwords every verso, lower left.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in nastaʻlīq in black ink; pointed.

decoNote: Illuminated headpiece in gold, blue, red and green with text on cloudbands; black and white flowers on light blue ground for intercolumnar fill (p. 2). Textblock is border-ruled in gold, and blue; columns are ruled in narrow gold; rubrications in red. Five full-page, color illustrations (p. 19, 138, 210, 229, 288).

binding.p: Bound in lacquered black boards (Type III) with birds and flowers painted in gold and gold frames; dark red leather spine; inside covers are painted dark red with a lighter red frame.
